<h2>Section 1: Executive Summary & Abstract</h2>
<h3>1.1 Project Introduction</h3>
<p>In modern cloud engineering, managing resource-heavy background processes (such as email processing, transaction verification, or content transcoding) requires an architecture that prevents duplicate work, tolerates node crashes, and schedules items dynamically. Codity is a containerized, multi-tenant distributed job scheduler designed to satisfy these conditions safely and concurrently.</p>

<h3>1.2 Core Problem Statement</h3>
<p>Traditional scheduling workflows suffer from duplicate execution bugs when multiple servers query a database for pending tasks concurrently. Codity resolves this by implementing atomic database-level locks, coupled with telemetry tracking to handle worker drops and automatic exponential-backoff retries.</p>

<h2>Section 2: System Architecture Design</h2>
<p>The project is structured as a TypeScript monorepo to guarantee interface consistency across API contracts:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>React Frontend Dashboard (Vite + Tailwind CSS):</strong> Offers clear visualization of cluster CPU load, queue capacities, live logs, and active worker nodes.</li>
  <li><strong>Express REST API Broker:</strong> Handles project management, job dispatches, and incoming worker telemetry signals.</li>
  <li><strong>Distributed Compute Worker:</strong> Multiple parallel worker scripts that poll the queue database, execute tasks, and send periodic health status reports.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Section 3: Concurrency Control & Database Locking</h2>
<h3>3.1 Preventing Race Conditions via SKIP LOCKED</h3>
<p>To support multiple compute nodes polling the database without claiming the same tasks, Codity executes an atomic query containing a <code>SKIP LOCKED</code> clause:</p>

<pre>
UPDATE "jobs"
SET "status" = 'RUNNING', "claimed_at" = NOW()
WHERE "id" IN (
    SELECT "id" FROM "jobs"
    WHERE "status" = 'PENDING' AND "run_at" <= NOW()
    ORDER BY "priority" DESC, "created_at" ASC
    LIMIT 1
    FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED
)
RETURNING *;
</pre>

<p>This query locks the target job row for the duration of the update transaction, instructing concurrent workers to ignore locked entries. This guarantees safe, duplicate-free execution without the overhead of external coordination clusters.</p>

<h3>3.2 Database Entity Schema</h3>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Entity Name</th>
      <th>Key Attributes</th>
      <th>Functional Role</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Users</strong></td>
      <td>id, email, passwordHash, firstName</td>
      <td>System operator profiles.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Projects</strong></td>
      <td>id, name, organizationId</td>
      <td>Logical project segregation.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Queues</strong></td>
      <td>id, name, concurrencyLimit, isPaused</td>
      <td>Task pipelines with load controllers.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Jobs</strong></td>
      <td>id, queueId, status, payload, runAt</td>
      <td>Active task payloads.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Workers</strong></td>
      <td>id, status, lastHeartbeat, cpuUsage</td>
      <td>Telemetry logs for cluster monitors.</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>Section 4: Security & Multi-Tenancy</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Access Authorization:</strong> Protected via JSON Web Tokens (JWT) inside secure, signed HttpOnly cookies.</li>
  <li><strong>Tenant Partitioning:</strong> Custom Express middleware validates that incoming tokens own the resource references in the current project context.</li>
  <li><strong>Body Sanitization:</strong> Integrated Zod schema validators to intercept and reject corrupt payload requests before database queries run.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Section 5: Testing & UI Theme Customization</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Automated Checks:</strong> Integrated Jest suites verifying routing access, tenant constraints, and user sessions.</li>
  <li><strong>Standard White Light Mode:</strong> Zero-lag UI theme toggler mapped to CSS Custom Properties, transitioning background nodes to pure white (<code>#F9FAFB</code>) and text to high-contrast dark gray (<code>#1F2937</code>) for optimal accessibility.</li>
</ul>

